title: Vikings Fall Late to Broncos
text:
Vikings Fall Late to Broncos 
  Vikings Fall Late to Broncos October 5, 2015 Updated Oct 5, 2015 at 12:14 AM CDT 
Denver, CO (NNCNOW.com) -- The Minnesota Vikings, despite a failing offensive line, kept pace for much of their contest with the Denver Broncosâ€”until a field goal doomed them. 
Denver's defensive front frequently tested the Vikings, leaving quarterback Teddy Bridgewater scrambling often (and being sacked). Denver running back Ronnie Hillman had a 72-yard touchdown run (the longest in the league so far this season). 
Harrison Smith's intercepting Peyton Manning led to the Vikings kicking a field goal to tie, but the Broncos responded with one of their own to win 23-20. 
The Vikings (2-2) will face Kansas City on October 18.
